avoid%20falling%20for%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20almost%20time%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamala-harris-donald-trump-15-days-swing-states-polling-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20presidential%20election%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20scammers%20are%20out%20in%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20most%20common%20scams%20around%20elections%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-avoid-election-scams-stay-safe-from-voter-registration-fraud-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evoter%20registration%20scams%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20fake%20surveys%20and%20polls%2C%20and%20political%20donation%20scams%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20of%20these%20scams%2C%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Secretaries%20of%20State%20says%20that%20scammers%20generally%20contact%20potential%20victims%20by%20phone%20or%20email%2C%20pretending%20to%20be%20a%20legitimate%20entity%2C%20like%20a%20political%20action%20committee%20or%20a%20state%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20spot%20an%20election%20scam%20in%20any%20of%20these%20instances%20is%20to%20stop%20and%20see%20if%20the%20person%20reaching%20out%20to%20you%20is%20asking%20for%20personal%20financial%20information.%20If%20they%20are%2C%20it's%20likely%20a%20scam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20signs%20that%20a%20donation%20request%20from%20a%20PAC%20could%20be%20fake%20are%20if%20they%20push%20you%20to%20donate%20quickly%20or%20if%20the%20website%20doesn't%20provide%20any%20contact%20information%2C%20NASS%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%2C%20scammers%20commonly%20use%20%26quot%3Bpressure%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20victims%20into%20uncomfortable%20situations.%C2%A0They%C2%A0will%20use%20phrases%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bact%20now!%26quot%3B%20to%20introduce%20a%20time%20element%20so%20that%20you%20don't%20have%20time%20to%20think%20about%20your%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPressuring%20you%20to%20act%20now%20is%20always%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20scam%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20FTC%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFake%20surveys%20and%20polls%20that%20prey%20on%20people's%20heightened%20emotions%20during%20election%20seasons%20are%20also%20common%2C%20NASS%20says.%20Signs%20that%20a%20survey%20or%20poll%20could%20be%20fake%20are%20if%20they%20offer%20compensation%20or%20prizes%20for%20participation%20or%20if%20they%20ask%20about%20controversial%20topics%20%26quot%3Bto%20rile%20you%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20spot%20a%20fake%20voter%20registration%20message%2C%20check%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20information%20you%20are%20receiving%20is%20coming%20from%20your%20official%20state%20or%20local%20election%20official%2C%20the%20agency%20says.%20Another%20common%20sign%20that%20a%20voter%20registration%20message%20could%20be%20a%20scam%20is%20if%20the%20messenger%20says%20you%20must%20pay%20to%20complete%20your%20voter%20registration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC%20recommends%20reporting%20any%20unsolicited%20texts%20or%20calls%20from%20someone%20who%20says%20they%20need%20your%20Social%20Security%20Number%20or%20financial%20information%20to%20register%20you%20to%20vote.%20If%20you%20think%20you%20may%20be%20the%20victim%20of%20a%20scam%2C%20you%20can%20visit%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconsumer.ftc.gov%2Ffeatures%2Fidentity-theft%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTC's%20identity%20theft%20recovery%20page%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20report%20the%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20register%20to%20vote%2C%20or%20to%20find%20out%20if%20your%20Social%20Security%20Number%20is%20required%20for%20voter%20registration%20in%20your%20state%2C%20the%20FTC%20says%20to%20contact%20your%20local%20election%20office%20or%20check%20the%20US%20Election%20Assistance%20Commission's%20National%20Voter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eac.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Feac_assets%2F1%2F6%2FFederal_Voter_Registration_ENG.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%