%2Fdropbox-ceo-drew-houston-ai-skills-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20home%20was%20damaged%20in%20Hurricane%20Milton.%20I%20was%20shocked%20at%20how%20fast%20FEMA%20sent%20me%20%249%2C200%20after%20I%20applied.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20enters%20a%20makeshift%20FEMA%20office%20with%20a%20sign%20in%20the%20window%20that%20reads%20%26quot%3BFEMA-STATE%20Disaster%20Recovery%20Center%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671bebad01ea6d83dee44693%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERetiree%20Rick%20Shiver%20says%20he%20recieved%20about%20%249%2C200%20from%20FEMA%20after%20Hurricane%20Milton.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%2FJeff%20Greenberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERick%20Shiver%20said%20Hurricane%20Milton%20damaged%20the%20awning%20and%20ductwork%20of%20his%20Port%20Orange%2C%20Florida%2C%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFEMA%20transferred%20him%20a%20total%20of%20%249%2C166%20for%20repairs%20eight%20days%20after%20he%20applied%20for%20aid%2C%20Shiver%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20feels%20lucky%20he%20got%20help%20so%20fast%20and%20plans%20to%20keep%20living%20in%20the%20area%2C%20unlike%20one%20of%20his%20neighbors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Rick%20Shiver%2C%20a%2072-year-old%20retired%20firefighter%20in%20Port%20Orange%2C%20part%20of%20the%20Daytona%20Beach%20metropolitan%20area%20on%20Florida's%20Atlantic%20Coast.%20The%20following%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20in%20Port%20Orange%2C%20Florida.%20I'm%20originally%20from%20St.%20Augustine%20and%20moved%20here%20five%20years%20ago.%20I%20was%20getting%20ready%20to%20start%20chemo%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20place%20where%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20do%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eyard%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20two-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20manufactured%20home%2C%20and%20I%20managed%20to%20get%20it%20for%20%2420%2C500.%20The%20previous%20owner%20had%20passed%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20I've%20ever%20evacuated.%20I%20was%20a%20firefighter%20in%20Daytona%20Beach%20for%2025%20years%2C%20and%20we%20were%20never%20allowed%20to%20because%20we%20always%20had%20to%20work%20during%20the%20storms.%20But%20this%20time%2C%20it%20kind%20of%20scared%20me.%20So%20I%20went%20to%20a%20little%20town%20called%20DeLand%2C%20just%20west%20of%20here%2C%20and%20stayed%20with%20my%20daughter%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20Port%20Orange%20area%20was%20underwater.%20There%20will%20be%20houses%20that%20will%20be%20demolished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20couldn't%20even%20get%20into%20my%20house%20for%20three%20days%20because%20the%20water%20was%20so%20high.%20When%20I%20finally%20could%2C%20I%20saw%20twisted%20metal%20from%20the%20awning.%20It%20used%20to%20stick%20out%20in%20the%20front%20of%20the%20house.%20It%20was%20completely%20gone%2C%20just%20a%20few%20upright%20posts%20still%20standing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22799%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20front%20of%20Rick%20Shiver's%20house%20following%20the%20storm%20with%20several%20%20inches%20of%20water%20blocking%20the%20entrance.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671bed839b3250dbbcea4f43%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22799%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERick%20Shiver's%20home%20in%20Port%20Orange%2C%20Florida%2C%20after%20Hurricane%20Milton.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rick%20Shiver%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20my%20house%20sits%20at%20the%20highest%20spot%20in%20the%20neighborhood%2C%20so%20my%20water%20damage%20was%20minimal%2C%20but%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20wind%20damage.%20My%20gutters%20were%20ripped%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20never%20applied%20for%20FEMA%20aid%20before.%20So%20I%20had%20no%20clue%20what%20to%20expect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d26ee4b-fd19-4561-a72a-77b5b8607660%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20shocked%20that%20I%20got%20money%20from%20FEMA%20so%20fast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20have%20electricity%20initially.%20Even%20when%20I%20did%2C%20from%20my%20generator%2C%20the%20Wi-Fi%20wasn't%20working.%20The%20day%20it%20came%20back%20on%2C%20I%20filed%20online%20with%20FEMA%20for%20money%20to%20repair%20the%20damage%20and%20wrote%20them%20a%20description.%20The%20answers%20were%20pretty%20cut-and-dried.%20They%20assigned%20me%20a%20case%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20submitted%20the%20application%20on%20Monday%2C%20October%2014.%20On%20October%2021%2C%20the%20inspector%20came%20by.%20He%20was%20here%20for%20about%2015%20minutes.%20The%20ductwork%20for%20the%20AC%20has%20to%20be%20completely%20taken%20out%20and%20replaced.%20The%20awning%20has%20to%20be%20rebuilt%20and%20all%20that%20metal%20replaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20took%20some%20pictures%2C%20looked%20everything%20over%2C%20and%20the%20next%20day%20I%20had%20money%20in%20the%20bank.%20That%20was%20eight%20days%20after%20I%20filed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltogether%2C%20I%20was%20given%20%249%2C166.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20clue%20how%20long%20it%20would%20take%20to%20get%20the%20money%2C%20but%20I%20was%20expecting%20it%20to%20be%20a%20month%20or%20two%20before%20I%20got%20anything%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20experienced%20damage%20from%20hurricanes%20or%20other%20disasters%20and%20applied%20for%20help%20from%20FEMA%3F%20We'd%20love%20to%20hear%20about%20it.%20Please%20email%20reporter%20Dan%20Latu%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Adlatu%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Edlatu%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20quickness%20helped%20%E2%80%94%20the%20air%20ducts%20will%20be%20moldy%20in%20there%20shortly%20if%20I%20don't%20get%20them%20fixed.%20And%20I'm%20not%20the%20least%20bit%20interested%20in%20breathing%20in%20mold%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20know%20if%20the%20%249%2C166%20will%20cover%20everything%2C%20but%20I%20can%20tell%20you%20it's%20going%20to%20help.%20I%20was%20really%20thankful%20for%20what%20I%20got.%20I've%20never%20gotten%20anything%20from%20the%20government%2C%20so%20this%20was%20nice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20don't%20have%20enough%20to%20do%20all%20the%20repairs%20that%20need%20to%20be%20done%2C%20then%20I'll%20just%20pay%20myself.%20But%20that's%20fine%2C%20I'm%20happy%20to%20have%20any%20help%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government's%20done%20a%20great%20job.%20I'm%20a%20registered%20Democrat%2C%20and%20I%20think%20the%20information%20being%20spread%20from%20a%20former%20president%20is%20all%20BS%2C%20because%20FEMA%20works%20and%20it%20works%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2297de18a1-2f29-4913-9c30-de67f730b66b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20might%20start%20to%20leave%20Florida%2C%20but%20I%20want%20to%20be%20near%20my%20grandkids%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20been%20fortunate.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20we've%20had%20a%20bunch%20of%20hurricanes%20and%20missed%20some%20bad%20ones.%20With%20how%20intense%20this%20flooding%20was%2C%20it's%20fortunate%20that%20we%20haven't%20had%20more%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20rough%20month.%20I%20believe%20people%20will%20be%20leaving%20this%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20neighbor%20came%20by%20after%20the%20storm.%20He%20could%20hear%20that%20I%20had%20a%20generator%20and%20knocked%20on%20my%20door%20asking%20if%20he%20could%20charge%20his%20phone.%20I%20let%20him%20in.%20When%20he%20was%20finished%2C%20he%20said%20they're%20moving%20back%20up%20to%20Pennsylvania.%20He%20said%20they%20can't%20take%20it%20anymore.%20He%20meant%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20initially%20thought%20I%20might%20need%20to%20move.%20I'm%2072%20and%20can't%20keep%20doing%20this%20every%20couple%20of%20years.%20But%20my%20children%20live%20here%2C%20I%20get%20to%20see%20my%20grandchildren.%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20move%20away%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-retiree-got-fema-disaster-relief-money-for-hurricane-damage-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730059562000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671bec40a0a0cc14f22423c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-retiree-got-fema-disaster-relief-money-for-hurricane-damage-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hurricane%20Milton%20damaged%20Rick%20Shiver's%20Florida%20home%2C%20but%20he%20got%20FEMA%20money%20quickly.%20He%20plans%20to%20make%20necessary%20repairs%20and%20keep%20living%20in%20Florida.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dlatu%40insider.com%20(Dan%20Latu)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A586%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-retiree-got-fema-disaster-relief-money-for-hurricane-damage-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chaos%20and%20political%20drama%20rock%20Japan's%20snap%20election%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730058662000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2Ff079%2Flive%2Ffaf03200-9498-11ef-8e6d-e3e64e16c628.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcx2nn16wrk2o%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prime%20Minister%20Shigeru%20Ishiba%20made%20a%20political%20gamble%2C%20and%20it%20backfired%2C%20leaving%20a%20weakened%20ruling%20party.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcx2nn16