t%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Panikoff%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Atlantic%20Council's%20Scowcroft%20Middle%20East%20Security%20Initiative%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fblogs%2Fnew-atlanticist%2Fexperts-react-israel-has-hit-back-at-iran-with-airstrikes-is-this-the-road-to-war-or-an-off-ramp%2F%3Futm_campaign%3Dread%26utm_content%3D20241026%26utm_medium%3Dorganic_social%26utm_source%3Dtwitter%26utm_term%3DAtlanticCouncil%23panikoff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20be%20a%20sign%20that%20Tehran%20%26quot%3Bis%20looking%20for%20an%20off-ramp%2C%20even%20if%20it%20claims%20otherwise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIran%20may%20be%20frustrated%20that%20its%20deterrence%20against%20Israel%20has%20waned%2C%20but%20it's%20unlikely%20to%20be%20temerarious%20in%20trying%20to%20restore%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F10%2F26%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fisrael-iran-attack-war.html%3Fsmid%3Dtw-nytimesworld%26smtyp%3Dcur%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Yoel%20Guzansky%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20National%20Security%20Studies%2C%20a%20Tel%20Aviv-based%20think%20tank%2C%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20music%20that%20I%20hear%20from%20Iran%20is%20basically%20saying%2C%20'Oh%2C%20this%20is%20nothing%2C'%26quot%3B%20but%20he%20added%20that%20it%20still%20marked%20the%20%26quot%3Bbeginning%20of%20a%20new%20phase%2C%20a%20dangerous%20one%2C%20with%20many%20more%20sensitivities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20possible%20for%20the%20two%20sides%20to%20close%20this%20round%20at%20least%2C%20and%20that%20we%20will%20not%20see%20an%20Iranian%20retaliation%20%E2%80%94%20or%20if%20we'll%20see%20it%2C%20it%20will%20be%20small%20in%20scale%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVoller%20said%20that%20should%20Iran%20choose%20to%20respond%2C%20it%20could%20turn%20to%20its%20proxies%20to%20defend%20its%20nuclear%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20must%20remember%20that%20Israel's%20end%20goal%20is%20to%20bring%20the%20Iranian%20nuclear%20program%20to%20an%20end%2C%20and%20any%20Iranian%20retaliation%20will%20provide%20Israel%20with%20the%20opportunity%20to%20continue%20pursuing%20this%20goal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ali%20Khamenei%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F553387f3eab8eab755514eaa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222071%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIran's%20supreme%20leader%2C%20Ayatollah%20Ali%20Khamenei.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FMorteza%20Nikoubazl%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fda12d17-0f2c-4f4f-994c-14dce3f2ec0d%5C%22%3EIsrael%20could%20strike%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVoller%20said%20Iran%20may%20be%20deterred%20from%20launching%20a%20direct%20counterattack%20because%20of%20Israel's%20track%20record%20and%20%26quot%3Bproven%20capability%20of%20reaching%20Iranian%20sensitive%20targets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20Israel's%20targeting%20of%20Iran's%20military%20sites%2C%20including%20its%20air%20defense%20system%2C%20would%20allow%20it%20to%20launch%20further%20air%20attacks%20if%20Iran%20were%20to%20escalate%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsrael%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20top%20military%20spenders%20as%20a%20share%20of%20GDP%2C%20and%20it%20receives%20large%20amounts%20of%20military%20aid%20from%20the%20US%20to%20maintain%20what%20it%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bqualitative%20military%20edge%26quot%3B%20over%20neighboring%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20recent%20events%20will%20likely%20have%20reinforced%20to%20Iran's%20leaders%20that%20the%20country%20is%20%26quot%3Bovermatched%20militarily%2C%26quot%3B%20Panikoff%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%2C%20for%20a%20regime%20that%20prioritizes%20stability%20above%20all%20else%2C%20makes%20entering%20into%20a%20full-scale%20war%20an%20illogical%20choice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20military%20has%20said%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bobligated%20to%20respond%26quot%3B%20if%20Iran%20attacked%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllie%20Geranmayeh%2C%20the%20deputy%20head%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20North%20Africa%20program%20at%20the%20European%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%2C%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20further%20attacks%20from%20Israel%20shouldn't%20be%20ruled%20out%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20US%20election%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20a%20sigh%20of%20relief%20across%20Iran%20and%20the%20region%20that%20the%20US%20managed%20to%20restrain%20Netanyahu%20for%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Geranmayeh%20said%2C%20referencing%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20the%20fear%20is%20that%20this%20is%20a%20temporary%20restraint%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20US%20elections.%20The%20'lame%20duck'%20phase%20ahead%20could%20be%20a%20moment%20where%20we%20see%20renewed%20Israeli%20attacks%20inside%20Iran%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20perceived%20golden%20window%20to%20further%20deplete%20Iranian%20capabilities%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-strikes-iran-middle-east-tensions-next-moves-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730051205000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F671e726a01ea6d83dee4671c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-strikes-iran-middle-east-tensions-next-moves-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Israeli%20military%20said%20it%20carried%20out%20%26quot%3Btargeted%20and%20precise%20strikes%26quot%3B%20on%20Iranian%20military%20sites%20on%20Saturday.%20Four%20Iranian%20soldiers%20were%20killed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mfriel