y%20interest%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20to%20today%20and%20I%20swim%20in%20a%20pool%20of%20regret.%20The%20economy%20has%20largely%20held%20up%2C%20and%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20continued%20on%20its%20tear%2C%20rising%20another%2022%25%20so%20far%20this%20year.%20Sure%2C%205.1%25%20return%20hasn't%20been%20bad.%20But%20who%20among%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-big-money-mistake-holding-cash-not-buying-stocks-investing-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethose%20of%20us%20keeping%20cash%20on%20the%20sidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20hasn't%20yearned%20for%20a%20taste%20of%20that%20sweet%20equity%20market%20nectar%20this%20year%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20not%20much%20has%20changed%20about%20my%20apprehension%20to%20get%20into%20stocks%2C%20even%20with%209-month%20rates%20from%20my%20credit%20union%20having%20fallen%20to%20a%20less-attractive%204.65%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20labor%20market%20has%20cooled%20to%20an%20almost-worrying%20degree%2C%20with%20the%20Sahm%20Rule%20recession%20indicator%20being%20triggered%20in%20August%20and%20statistics%20like%20quits%2C%20hires%2C%20and%20the%20year-over-year%20change%20in%20full-time%20employees%20all%20falling%20significantly%2C%20as%20they%20have%20in%20prior%20recessions.%20Payroll%20revisions%20have%20also%20been%20significantly%20to%20the%20downside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20while%2C%20the%20market%20has%20stamped%20even%20higher%20highs%2C%20and%20some%20measures%20show%20market%20valuations%20rival%20the%20most%20expensive%20levels%20in%20history.%20Both%20Goldman%20Sachs%20and%20Bank%20of%20America%20have%20warned%20of%20a%20decade%20of%20dismal%20returns%20ahead%2C%20with%20Goldman%20saying%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20likely%20to%20underperform%20the%204.2%25%20yield%20on%20risk-free%2010-year%20Treasurys%20on%20an%20annualized%20returns%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoping%20not%20to%20lose%20my%20money%20in%20a%20potential%20stock-market%20reversal%2C%20but%20also%20hoping%20to%20not%20miss%20out%20further%20on%20what%20have%20been%20ridiculously%20good%20returns%20(I%20want%20it%20all%2C%20what%20can%20I%20say)%2C%20I%20called%20up%20a%20few%20financial%20advisors%20and%20market%20experts%20and%20solicited%20some%20free%20advice%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20writing%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProbably%20the%20most%20important%20variable%20of%20coming%20up%20with%20an%20investing%20plan%20is%20establishing%20a%20timeline.%20I%20just%20turned%2030%20years%20old%2C%20so%20I'll%20probably%20keep%20my%20money%20invested%20for%20a%20few%20decades.%20That%20is%2C%20unless%20I%20need%20it%20for%20a%20down%20payment%20or%20something%20in%20five%20years%20%E2%80%94%20like%20I%20said%2C%20I%20want%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Johnson%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20Creighton%20University%2C%20was%20quick%20to%20remind%20me%20I%20can't%2C%20telling%20me%20that%20my%20timeline%20isn't%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20decades%20if%20I%20really%20need%20the%20money%20in%20a%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20I%20was%20serious%20about%20keeping%20my%20money%20in%20the%20market%20for%20the%20long-term%2C%20Johnson%20said%2C%20then%20there's%20no%20real%20bad%20time%20to%20enter%20the%20market.%20In%20another%2030-years'%20time%2C%20the%20market%20is%20very%20likely%20to%20have%20gone%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20he%20said%20it's%20probably%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20commit%20the%20entire%20small%20chunk%20of%20change%20I've%20saved%20up%20to%20the%20market%20right%20now%2C%20let%20it%20sit%2C%20and%20continue%20adding%20money%20every%20month%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20wasn't%20fully%20convinced.%20On%20my%20beat%2C%20I%20cover%20the%20outlooks%20of%20well-known%20market%20minds%20like%20GMO%20Cofounder%20Jeremy%20Grantham%2C%20top%201%25%20fund%20manager%20Bill%20Smead%2C%20and%20many%20more.%20Some%20of%20them%20lay%20out%20bearish%20arguments%2C%20and%20like%20Goldman%20and%20Bank%20of%20America%20have%20pointed%20out%2C%20Grantham%20and%20Smead%20have%20also%20said%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20set%20to%20deliver%20abysmal%20returns%20in%20the%20next%20decade%20if%20you%20were%20to%20invest%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20starting%20points%20matter%20a%20lot%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20valuations.%20Bank%20of%20America%20says%20they%20determine%2080%25%20of%20the%20market's%20return%20over%20a%20decade.%20If%20you%20had%20bought%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%20in%202000%2C%20you%20would%20have%20suffered%20a%2028%25%20loss%20going%20out%20exactly%20a%20decade%20to%20August%202010.%20And%20you%20still%20would%20have%20had%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20money%20you%20started%20with%20all%20the%20way%20in%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20to%20buy%20low%20and%20sell%20high%2C%20not%20buy%20high%20and%20%3Cem%3Eeventually%3C%2Fem%3E%20sell%20higher!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20multiple%20decades%20down%20the%20line%2C%20the%20returns%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20good%20no%20matter%20what.%20Today%2C%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20285%25%20from%20the%20height%20of%20the%20dot-com%20bubble.%20%3Cem%3EBut%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20if%20you%20had%20waited%20until%20market%20lows%20in%202002%20to%20buy%2C%20your%20position%20would%20be%20up%20587%25%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpressing%20my%20concerns%20about%20valuations%20and%20what%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20deteriorating%20labor%20market%2C%20Johnson%20stopped%20me%20and%20reiterated%20in%20a%20tough-love%20tone%20my%20long-term%20timeline.%20He%20also%20said%20there's%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20where%20the%20top%20is%2C%20and%20reminded%20me%20of%20the%2022%25%20returns%20I've%20missed%20out%20on%20so%20far%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETouch%C3%A9%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20play%20the%20what-if%20game%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20go%20to%20cash%20or%20you%20go%20to%20less%20risky%20assets%2C%20your%20opportunity%20loss%20in%20returns%20is%20huge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20a%20way%20for%20me%20to%20play%20both%20sides%2C%20according%20to%20Ryan%20Marshall%2C%20a%20financial%20advisor%20at%20Wealth%20Enhancement%20Group%2C%20which%20manages%20upward%20of%20%2496%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20put%20a%20portion%20of%20my%20money%20into%20stocks%20right%20now%2C%20while%20also%20laddering%20the%20other%20part%20in%20different%20CD%20durations.%20So%2C%20for%20example%2C%20I%20could%20plug%2025%25%20of%20the%20money%20into%20stocks%2C%2025%25%20of%20it%20in%20a%203-month%20CD%2C%2025%25%20in%20a%206-month%20CD%2C%20and%2025%25%20in%20a%209-month%20CD.%20As%20each%20of%20those%20CDs%20expires%2C%20I%20could%20then%20put%20that%20money%20to%20work%20in%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20market%20goes%20up%20during%20that%20time%2C%20oh%20well%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20I%20had%20some%20exposure%2C%20and%20I%20was%20still%20collecting%20pretty%20decent%20interest%20in%20the%20CDs.%20If%20the%20market%20goes%20down%2C%20even%20better%20%E2%80%94%20I%20can%20buy%20in%20at%20a%20cheaper%20entry%20point%2C%20plus%20I%20made%20some%20interest%20in%20the%20meantime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Browne%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Alexis%20Investment%20Partners%2C%20went%20even%20further.%20Instead%20of%20buying%20CDs%2C%20buy%20the%20duration%20equivalents%20in%20Treasury%20bills.%20They're%20more%20liquid%2C%20so%20I%20can%20sell%20them%20in%20the%20blink%20of%20an%20eye%20if%20I%20need%20to%2C%20while%20also%20keeping%20the%20interest%20paid%20up%20to%20that%20point.%20With%20CDs%2C%20usually%20you%20have%20to%20give%20back%20the%20interest%20if%20you%20exit%20it%20before%20the%20expiration%20date.%20Plus%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20pay%20state%20tax%20on%20interest%20from%20Treasurys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20man%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20have%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20still%20not%20entirely%20decid